			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="2918">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>With the publication of William Penrod&rsquo;s collected letters [&ldquo;<a href="/article/1643">In Rejection I Remain</a>,&rdquo; July 1995], <strong>The Sun</strong> &mdash; a community, a conversation, a magazine written by its readers and read by its writers &mdash; has reached new heights (depths?) of interactivity. Who needs the Internet?</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Annie Gottlieb<br>New York, New York</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

